{% extends "_base.html.jinja" %}

{# Aging WIP is a "right now" snapshot pinned to the latest
   materialise — it does not follow the Period picker, so there
   is no Period filter bar on this page. #}
{% block filter_bar %}{% endblock %}

{% block content %}
  {% with summary = {"title": "Aging WIP", "headline": aging.headline} %}
    {% include "_partials/metric_summary.html.jinja" %}
  {% endwith %}

  {% with mode = 'detail', data = aging %}
    {% include "_partials/aging_tile.html.jinja" %}
  {% endwith %}

  {% with data = work_items %}
    {% include "_partials/work_items_table.html.jinja" %}
  {% endwith %}

  <details class="detail-extras">
    <summary>Help · how to read, what to do next</summary>
    <h2>How to read this</h2>
    <p>
      Each point is one in-flight item plotted at its current
      state (x) against its elapsed age in days (y). Dashed lines
      are empirical percentiles of completed-item cycle times:
      P50, P85, P95. A <em>"right now"</em> snapshot — pinned
      to the latest materialise, not the Period picker.
    </p>
    <ul>
      <li>Items above <strong>P85</strong> are statistically
        unlikely to finish within the standard cycle-time
        commitment — they need attention today.</li>
      <li>Items above <strong>P95</strong> are deep-tail
        outliers; expect them to need re-scoping, splitting,
        or escalation, not just patience.</li>
      <li>A cluster of aging items in one stage points at a
        bottleneck in that stage, not the items themselves.</li>
    </ul>

    <h2>Possible next steps</h2>
    <p>
      "Stop starting, start finishing" — work the oldest item
      first.
    </p>
    <ul>
      <li>Open standup with the rightmost / oldest point: what's
        blocking it, and what would unblock it today?</li>
      <li>Items breaching P85: split the work, swarm it, or
        explicitly accept the new forecast and tell stakeholders.</li>
      <li>Items breaching P95: assume it won't finish as scoped
        — re-plan rather than wait it out.</li>
    </ul>
  </details>

  <a class="back-link" href="{{ ("/workflows/" ~ contract.name ~ "/") | keep_filters }}">← Back to dashboard</a>
{% endblock %}
